<http://www.spektrix.com/nationalmusiccentre/event/174402AQHQHRLNJKHNSKCNKLRBDJJKLPV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Reverberations: Chopin Reframed";
  schema:description """
	Experience a piano masterpiece… reimagined. Known for performances of imagination, intensity, and individuality, 2025 Honens Gold Laureate Élisabeth Pion returns to Calgary with Frédéric Chopin’s Études Op. 25. This time, she presents the piece with a poetic and fiery twist—interspersed with works of shimmering reflections and bold clarity from other composers.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>After the concert, hop across the street for Bison Noir: Revisions in Real-Time at 9 pm at the historic King Eddy.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Studio+Bell,+home+of+the+National+Music+Centre/@51.0445506,-114.054786,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x53717aaa864fd43b:0x7609799479e4d20e!8m2!3d51.0445591!4d-114.0529828\">Studio Bell, 850 4 Street SE Calgary</a><span><br/></span>Doors: 6:00 pm. Show: 7:00 pm.<span><br/></span>Adult: $66 <span><br/></span>Senior (65+): $54 <span><br/></span>Student A440 Club (18-39): $25 <span><br/></span>Youth (7-17):$10<span><br/></span>+ GST<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>NMC Members get 15% off tickets. Sign in with the email address associated with your membership to have your tickets auto-discount.
""";
